(2, 'DCF', 'The DCF is a state of art inhouse computer facility for Physics Department students. It caters to undergraduate and postgraduate students like Engineering Physics, Dual Degree Program and Masters. PhD students can also use this facility for their computational needs. DCF has around 50 desktops for taking courses such as PH5730 Methods of Computational Physics, PH2140 Mathematics on the computer and PH5060 Physics Lab I (PG), and PH5120 Physics Lab II (PG). Recently DCF has been going under renovation, which will lead to an increase in the number of systems. Computational facilities will also boost with new workstations and clusters in place.', '', 'Mr. Varun (varunv@iitm.ac.in)', 1, 'admin@mail.com', '2022-09-26 12:18:34');
