(21, 97, 89, 0, '', '', '1.jpg', '2.jpg', '', 'Our research group is interested in developing new quantum devices using recently discovered topological magnetic, superconducting, and 2D  quantum materials. We are a new research group. The group is determined to uncover new quantum technologies by developing micro-and nanoscale quantum devices. Our group is in the process of developing state-of-the-art thin-film growth, nanofabrication, and low-temperature magnetotransport, and magneto-optical techniques. Presently, we are working on an emerging new research area called Weyltronics. Our present focus is to study topological Dirac and Weyl semimetal thin films and explore their exotic electrical, thermal, and optical properties under electric, magnetic, and strain fields. ', '1', '3', '2022-03-15 02:00:25'),
(22, 35, 90, 0, '', '', 'OTOCscreenshot.png', 'AME46state.png', '', 'Research interests are in theoretical aspects of dynamical systems, Hamiltonian and quantum chaotic systems, quantum information, especially  entanglement, quantum walks, many-body physics, including MBL, ETH and thermalization, random matrix theory and its applications. Quantum combinatorics,  OTOCs, tensor networks and dual quantum circuits are some recent (2021) aspects of my work. ', '1', '3', '2022-03-15 04:17:28'),
(23, 39, 91, 0, '', '', 'JPP image1-basu.png', 'my lab-basu.png', '', 'We are an upcoming group in the Physics department of IIT Madras with primary emphasis on Optical Tweezers based study of statistical mechanics and biological systems. We are essentially going to divide our time for two topics, namely, High Resolution Imaging based systems and Optical Tweezers based systems. We would like to couple high resolution imaging systems to optical tweezers to study biological systems. Optical Tweezers are a tightly focused beam of light which generates a three dimensional potential well for trapping microparticles. These can not only be used to apply and detect controlled forces but also controlled torques upon using birefringent microparticles. We would like to couple single cells to the optical tweezers, to probe both inside the cell and on the membrane. We would also like to enhance optical tweezers intrumentation to sense forces on cells passively without actually applying a force directly.', '1', '3', '2022-03-12 01:11:38'),
(24, 45, 92, 19, '', '', 'For website.PNG', '', '', 'Our group works on experimental high-energy physics at various accelerator laboratories around the world: KEK (Japan), IHEP (China) and CERN (Switzerland). We primarily study the weak interaction between quarks (flavour physics) making measurements related to matter-antimatter asymmetry in the decays of charm and beauty quarks. We also collaborate with Profs. Behera and Pujahari on the CMS experiment at CERN. ', '1', '19', '2023-03-01 12:12:08'),
(25, 85, 93, 0, '', '', '', '', '', 'We explore the physics of nanoscale devices and their applications in emerging technologies including electronic (ferroelectric non-volatile memory and logic devices), optoelectronics (UV& Broadband photodetectors and random lasers) and quantum technologies. We understand the physics of 2D semiconductors and 3D oxide interfaces and develop new functional devices. We develop the processes for the integration of heterogeneous functional materials and devices.', '1', '3', '2021-12-09 02:44:23'),
(26, 50, 94, 0, '', '', 'plot_1.png', 'plot_2.png', '', 'Current Research Interests areÂ  Dynamical Systems Theory, Quantum Dynamics, Quantum Optics, and QuantumI Information and Computation.Optical tomogramsÂ  and qubit tomograms are used to directly identifyÂ nonclassical effects such as squeezing andÂ  higher-order squeezingÂ  of quantum states and quantum entanglementÂ  between subsystem states as the full system evolves under a Hamiltonian.Â  This program circumvents elaborate state reconstruction. Research in the interface of Dynamical Systems and Quantum DynamicsÂ  involves tracking the ergodicity properties of quantum observables using tools from Classical Dynamical Systems theory. The various focus areas in the group are state reconstruction, classical and quantum entanglement, wavepacket revival phenomena in quantum systems, open quantum systems and decoherence,Â  The IBM quantum computing platform is used to examine nonclassical properties of optical states and spin systems by employingÂ appropriate equivalent circuits. ', '1', '3', '2021-12-10 11:24:18'),
(27, 36, 95, 0, '', '', 'm-research.jpg', '', '', 'We explore to understand the ferroelectric and magnetic perovskite oxides in bulk, composites, heterostructures and multilayer thin film assemblies for thier multifunctional characteristics. Ferroelectric photovoltaics, electrocaloric, magnetocaloric, energy storage, electro and photo-strictions are the priority areas of research in our group.', '1', '3', '2022-03-14 06:54:08'),
(28, 59, 96, 0, '', '', '', '', '', 'Research interests include theoretical aspects of Quantum Error Correction, Quantum Information Theory and Quantum Networks. Currently, we are exploring error mitigaton techniques for near-term (NISQ) devices as well as developing techniques and protocols for building robust, scalable quantum communication networks. We are also working on aspects of quantum information theory that are useful in the study and chaarcterization of quantum many-body systems, such as entanglement growth and operator spreading.', '1', '3', '2021-12-09 02:46:12'),
(29, 60, 97, 0, '', '', 'CERN_CMS-2.jpg', 'CMS-HIN-17-004_Figure_001.png', '', 'The research interests of my group are focused on understanding high energy density Quantum Chromodynamics (QCD) created in relativistic heavy ion collisions at the Large Hadron Collider (LHC). QCD calculations predict that a transition from normal nuclear matter to a deconfined phase of matter consisting of strongly interacting quarks and gluons, known as the Quark-Gluon Plasma (QGP), will occur at extremely high temperature and energy densities. My group is currently involved in the CMS experiment at the LHC, CERN. Research activities focus on the use of soft scattering processes to identify the properties of QGP utilizing heavy ions and search for the possibilities of QGP in high multiplicity small ion collisions which is possible due to the state-of-the-art instrumentation in LHC. In addition, my group is currently involved in the CMS Tracker detector upgradation in collaboration with Prof. Behera and Libby. Also, we are actively participating in design of comprehensive experiments for the forthcoming Electron Ion Collider (EIC) and CBM experiment at FAIR.  ', '1', '3', '2021-12-10 11:39:52'),
(30, 61, 98, 0, '', '', '', '', '', 'My reseach focuses on the development of particle detector for current and future experiments and explores it applicability in imaging. I am currently focusing on research and  development of next generation silicon sensor for future application. This work is in collaboration with CERN detector research group. My group along with Prof.s Libby and Pujahari working for silicon tracking detector upgrade for Compact Muon Solenoid (CMS) experiment in Geneva, Switzerland. My physics interests are Higgs physics, BSM, lepton universalilty using tau lepton and g-2 for tau lepton and CP violation in Bs decays using CMS experiment.  I have keen interest in setting up experiment in India like India-based Neutrino Observatory (INO) and have been active member of INO collaboration since 2011.', '1', '3', '2021-12-09 02:47:24'),
(31, 62, 99, 0, '', '', 'padhan-3.png', 'padhan-5.png', '', 'My research focuses on interface physics in thin films, thin film multilayers and superlattices. My group is involved in (i) fabrication and study of transition metal oxides materials, (ii) fabrication, processing and measurement of electronic transport of transition metal oxides based junctions, and (iii) corresponding device engineering. We also synthesize and characterize nanostructures of transition metal chalcogenides and oxides materials, i.e., nanoparticles. In addition, we perform theoretical condense matter physics calculations, like band structure and spin texture simulations using first principles density functional theory.', '1', '3', '2021-12-10 12:01:07'),
(32, 64, 100, 0, '', '', '', '', '', 'We emphasize on â€˜hands onâ€™ training on time-domain photophysics, nonlinear optics & fluorescence microscopy. The entire focus is on imparting the experimental skills to the students that generally go parallel to the black-box, push-button technology. Along with the â€˜fabrication-developmentâ€™ activity, the students are motivated to take up the numerical modelling of the phenomena under studies on contemporary-interdisciplinary topics. The relaxation of the entity known as the â€œexcited stateâ€ achieved via photoexcitation - is the single point agenda. The phenomena under investigation are â€œultrafast relaxation processes with laser-induced transient grating, Z-scan and phase conjugation techniquesâ€ and properties of â€œwhispering gallery modesâ€ of symmetric structures embedded with fluorescent materials. The resonance excitation-energy transfer and electron transfer processes are often encountered in the systems while interacting with the non-fluorescent or, low-dimensional materials.', '1', '3', '2021-12-09 02:48:23'),
(33, 63, 101, 0, '', '', '', '', '', 'My research focuses on traversable wormholes, hidden symmetries in Einstein equations in the presence of a Killing vector, uniqueness of supersymmetric black holes, attractor mechanism, non-supersymmetric attractors and their stability, multiple attractors. Attractor mechanism plays a very crucial role in understanding the black hole entropy. In particular it explains why the entropy of black holes depend only on the quantized charges of the black hole and not on any continuous parameter such as the moduli associated with the vector multiplets and hyper multiplets. Of particular interest is the issue involving the multiplicity of attractors, i.e., the existence of different attractor points with the same value of charges. This has important consequence in describing the microscopic entropy of black holes. We focus on studying multiple attractors in different string theory compactifications.', '1', '3', '2021-12-09 02:48:48'),
(34, 84, 102, 0, '', '', 'Pramoda Group Rsearch Summary_1.jpg', '', '', 'My research group is focused on  synthesis of several 2D quantum materials including transition metal dichalcogenides (TMDs), Topological Insulators (TIs) and anisotropic layered materials using  mechanical exfoliation and chemical vapor deposition (CVD) and to explore the emerging quantum phenomena.  We  fabricate in-plane as well as van der Waals heterostructures made out of these materials for different inter-layer rotation, which leads to an immersing field known as Twistronics. In addition, we also work on technology development using 2D membranes  for non-intermittent renewable energy generation (Blue Energy) using salinity gradient.', '1', '3', '2022-03-15 12:44:39'),
(35, 73, 103, 0, '', '', 'Bare and Graphene Oxide Wrapped TiO2 Nanotubes.jpg', 'Single CuO nanowire devices for charge transport studies.jpg', 'Ion beam modification of TiO2 nanorods.jpg', 'The focus of our current research is on the growth of one-dimensional metal oxide nanostructures, thin films and heterostructures for solar energy (photocatalysis) and chemical sensing applications. Our expertise lies in direct growth of vertically oriented nanostructures and their composites with 2D materials; photoelectrochemical water splitting for hydrogen generation, photocatalytic CO2 reduction; sensors and electronic nose for gas detection etc. Recently, we have also ventured into the study of charge transport in single nanostructures and interesting features and anomalies have been discovered. In addition, we have explored high energy ion-beam induced modifications in nanomaterials in collaboration with IUAC Delhi. Facilities in our laboratory include various nanomaterials and thin film deposition systems such as thermal evaporation, RF-DC sputtering, Sol-Gel spin coating, Hydrothermal  and Electrochemical workstation etc. We also have photoelectrochemical set-up equipped with solar simulator; semi-automated, computer interfaced gas sensing set-up; gas chromatograph etc.', '1', '3', '2022-04-16 12:21:52'),
(36, 79, 104, 0, '', '', '', '', '', 'I work primarily in the area of hep-th. My interests over the last decade has been on the microscopic counting of BPS states in string theory. This work has found connections with several areas of physics and mathematics such as Statistical Mechanics, Number Theory, Lie Algebras and Combinatorics. A fascinating discovery of my group was to find a connection between the largest Mathieu group and the counting of BPS states in N=4 supersymmetric string theory. Currently I am working on extending the counting of BPS states to N=2 string theory. I am also beginning to work on the use of measures of quantum information such as entanglement entropy in quantum and conformal field theories using holographic methods. I also have a long-standing interest in all aspects of higher dimensional partitions. In 2012, I started the partitions project to get IITM undergraduates involved in research.', '1', '3', '2021-12-09 02:52:08'),
(37, 80, 105, 0, '', '', '', '', '', 'My research interests involve quantum and classical dynamical systems, chaos (quantum and classical), quantum information and computation and physics of complex systems especially topics from ecology and evolution.', '1', '3', '2021-12-09 02:52:55'),
(38, 99, 106, 0, '', '', 'banner_rsingh.jpeg', '', '', 'My research is in the area of soft matter physics. With this principal theme, I study problems in statistical mechanics, fluid mechanics, and biophysics. Much of my current focus is on studying active particle suspensions. Active particles - such as microorganisms and synthetic microswimmers -  are a class of colloids that create fluid flow even when they are stationary. Current research directions include: (a) studying the role of fluid-mediated interactions in determining the collective dynamics of active particles and (b) building continuum theories of active matter systems.', '1', '3', '2021-12-10 12:30:16'),
(39, 38, 107, 0, '', '', '', '', '', 'I work on various fundamental questions at the interface of quantum field theory, classical and quantum gravity, and quantum information theory.  I am also very interested in applications to quantum many-body physics and quantum computation.', '1', '3', '2022-03-12 11:56:59'),
(40, 49, 108, 0, '', '', '', '', '', 'I am the Principal Investigator for the pCoE initiative titled, â€œMillimeter & Microwave Metamaterialsâ€.', '1', '3', '2022-03-12 03:09:36'),
(41, 57, 109, 31, '', '', '', '', '', 'The quantum materials group focuses on the design, growth, and investigation of novel quantum materials that are promising to host rich and diverse electronic and magnetic phenomena with exotic quasiparticle excitations. The entangled states with fractional excitations in quantum materials may provide essential ingredients to address some of the fundamental questions in condensed matter.', '1', '31', '2023-03-05 09:50:04'),
(42, 116, 110, 0, '', '', 'Picture1.png', 'Picture2.png', 'Picture3.png', 'Quantum optics deals with the interaction of individual quanta of light, known as photons,\r\nwith atoms and molecules. Now, it has been increasingly studied with the solid state\r\nplatforms and constitutes the key ingredients such as non-classical light, quantum\r\nteleportation and quantum transduction of quantum computation and quantum metrology.\r\nAlong this direction, we model and investigate the interaction of light with solid state\r\nplatforms such as quantum dots (QDs) and hybrid quantum systems for the generation of\r\nsingle- and entangled photons, squeezed light and coherent microwave (optical) to optical\r\n(microwave) conversion.', '1', '3', '2022-07-21 12:50:17'),
(43, 115, 111, 0, '', '', '', '', '', 'The Universe changes its phase from the completely neutral stage to ionization state by the radiation of the first source and galaxies. This is one of the important milestone in evolution history named as the Epoch of Reionization (EoR). The 21-cm line emission from the neutral hydrogen (HI) is an important tool to study this epoch. A lot of astrophysical and cosmological information such as timing, duration of the epoch, the properties, and the evolution of the first stars and galaxies can be revealed using this 21-cm line.The two next-generation telescopes, the <br /><br />\r\n<a href=\"https://reionization.org/\"> Hydrogen Epoch of Reionization Array (HERA)</a>  and the <a href=\"https://www.skatelescope.org/\"> Square Kilometre Array (SKA)</a>, are expected to detect it for the very first time, and this will open up an entirely new observational window to probe the first stars and galaxies. We are working on simulation, develop statistical algorithms, and also analyze the real data to unveil the evolution history of the Universe using 21-cm radiation.', '1', '3', '2022-07-21 12:35:13'),
(44, 118, 112, 0, '', '', '', '', '', 'Dielectric metamaterials,Nonlinear absorption and high-intensity light propagation in semiconductors,Minority carrier and spin relaxation lifetimes in semiconductors,Modeling of infrared devices, avalanche photodiodes, resonant tunneling devices, power devices, spin field effect transistors, magnetic sensors, and CdTe solar cells\r\nHigh-field transport in submicron devices,  and optical properties of semiconductors\r\nModeling MBE growth\r\nEmpirical and first-principles (LCAO) band structures, and optical, electrical, and electronics properties of semiconductor compounds, alloys, and superlattices', '1', '3', '2022-10-15 12:56:58');
